You are given a task to tell whether the number is pure or not. A pure number is a number whose sum of digits is multiple of 3.

O(1) time and O(1) space

Input Description:
You are given a number n.

Output Description:
Print yes if it is pure else not

Sample Input :
13
Sample Output :
not

      N = int(input())
      sum = 0
      for i in str(N):
          sum+= int(i)
      if sum%3 ==0 :
          print("yes")
      else:
          print("not")


OR

N = input()
num = sum(list(map(int,N)))
print("yes") if num %3 ==0 else print("not")
